message: The grammar was definitely off here. Venosus is an adjective and has to match the declension of the corresponding noun (singular nominative), "venosi" is the singular genitive or plural nominative form of "venosus". "Vertebrales" is the plural M/F form of "vertebralis", the original author probably meant do decline the adjective in the genitive case, but even the genitive of vertebralis is still "vertebralis". The change "interni"→"internus" has the same explanation as for "venosi"→"venosus".
